# MinIO IAM split — content-control sibling pod's password.
# ADR-048 PR-B7.
#
# This user is bound to the `content_control` policy provisioned by
# `charts/audittrace/templates/minio/job-bucket-init.yaml`:
#   GET/DEL  quarantine/*           (allowed — read + delete after scan)
#   PUT      episodic/papers/*      (allowed — promotion target)
#   GET      procedural/*           (DENIED — operator data is off-limits)
#   GET      trust-store/*          (DENIED — chain-of-trust is off-limits)
#
# The audittrace-content-control sibling repo's chart consumes
# this password via Vault Agent annotations on the deployment;
# the Vault path is read at pod startup.
#
# 1. Generate a strong password (`openssl rand -base64 32`).
# 2. Save as ./secrets/minio_content_control_password.txt.
# 3. Run `make k8s-bootstrap-secrets`. Lands at:
#    - Vault: kv/audittrace/minio/content_control (key: password)
#    - k8s Secret: <release>-minio-iam (content_control_password)
REPLACE_WITH_STRONG_PASSWORD
